Joram Piatigorsky (born February 24, 1940) is an American molecular biologist and eye researcher at the National Institutes of Health. He was a NIH Distinguished Scientist and the founding Chief of the Laboratory of Molecular and Developmental Biology at the National Eye Institute (1981â€“2009), before stepping down and becoming an NEI Scientist Emeritus.
He is the son of Gregor Piatigorsky and Jacqueline de Rothschild.
